Sculptor-> Object List

"Object List" is used to find objects by name. This tool can be used
to "grab" objects singly or in groups for selection. This is very
handy in densely packed scenes where it would be difficult to "reach
through" to a particular object or group of objects.

Once you have activated the object list you may use it as an alternate
selection tool, you may also use it to select and rename objects as
you build a complex scene. Select an object by clicking on the object
name in the list. Deselect by clicking on it again. You can select
more than one object by clicking on the names one by one. The selected
object names will be highlighted.

Once an object is selected from with in "Object List" it will be
treated as if it had been selected in the active window and any
operation which would act upon a selected object using the mouse
cursor will work the normal way.
